\displaystyle{\begin{aligned}
   \frac{35}{36} - \frac{5}{9}
        \amp =  \frac{35}{36} - \frac{20}{36} \\
        \amp = \frac{35 - 20}{36} \\
        \amp = \frac{15}{36} \amp  \hbox{We can reduce this by dividing 3 into both the numerator and the denominator.
}\\
        \amp = \frac{5}{12}
